Honestly a cute library so many nice programs and staff but I hate how they always close LAST minute on snow days. Everyone else in town closes early or at least with an 1-2 hour notice. They literally wait 5 minutes before deciding to close when they know they had scheduled programs. I even emailed early today to ask them to please give more of a notice if they were to close and they confirmed it was still open until close at 5:58pm and they waited until 10 minutes after book club started at 6pm to decide they were closing at 6:20 on the dot. Super inconsiderate considering they will make you wait outside for your ride in the cold dark snow. Honestly I know they wanted to get home but making me feel like a burden when YALL decided to close last minute with no warning twice during or right before an event that I got confirmation for 2 minutes before class started is rude in my opinion. They could have let me wait inside a few more extra minutes. I called my ride as soon as they let me know, and next time I will make sure they wait outside for me or inside because they are so inconsistent. Actually if it’s raining or even so much as snowing a pinch I won’t even show up

reviews_data.review_text:
I've switched entirely to e-books, so I don't come to the library often anymore. I still use my card for e-books, I just don't need to visit in person to do that.

Pretty much the only reason I come to the library is because I need to print something. Who has a printer? Not me. Printing was free for a bit at the library which was nice, but they've started charging again. It's only 25 cents per page for black and white and 50 cents per page for color which is well worth not having to deal with a printer for me.

This isn't my normal library, but it was on our way when we were running errands so we stopped here instead. There's a convenient app you can use to upload and print your documents. The reason for the lower than normal rating here is because none of the librarians knew how to use it.

The app is straightforward if you're adding a printer for the first time. Unfortunately, I had my normal library set up already and couldn't figure out how to add another library. The librarians only seemed to know how to repeat the instructions on the sign (which assumed you had never set up a printer before).

I ended up having to email the stuff to myself, log into a computer, and print from there which is more time consuming. The computers also turn off immediately 10 minutes before it closes so I was in a race with the clock. It shut down seconds after I clicked print.

I hope they get the issues with the app resolved so you can have more than one library (or inform staff how to do that). Until then, I'll stick to my normal library.

The library itself is OK - kinda small, but you can always request tons of stuff. However, my car got keyed (apparently randomly - I hadn't encountered anyone) in front of a security camera but security seemed unsurprised and didn't follow up about it. Now I don't feel comfortable coming here, especially with my kids, if arbitrary vandalism in the parking lot is considered normal and tolerated.

I must say from the beginning that this might be a biased review only because I have two children under the age of 5. So when I go to a library I'm not necessarily looking for peace and quiet but more an educational activity or experience for children. They have a good selection of books for all ages. A really cool preteen gaming section. They have tons of books in African American literature. Those who have a lot of nice brand new novels and DVDs which I liked. But it seemed like this would be more appropriate for pre teens and adults. They have a good number of computers for internet access. But only two computers for children use only. Library staff was helpful but not super friendly.
Best North Carolina library.
Convenient and quiet

They have a few, but not many puzzles.
Scavenger hunts and word games available sometimes for older kids.
Parking lot is small, but never a problem on normal days.
Restrooms are nice, clean and updated. However, there is no changing table.
It's a good Library

Awesome!!!
